Imagery Description: (a) WhiteNon Sepcifiedfleshed woman sitting on lap of, and embracing, halfNon Sepcifieddraped youth, Eros to right binds a fillet around them, (b) two nude whiteNon Sepcifiedfleshed women at a laver, left taking clothing from a box, right holding up mirror; whiteNon Sepcifiedfleshed female head looking down from window above to left; to left, below handle, seated Pan with lagobolon, bird flying above. Lid (one handle missing)—on the squat lekythos which serves as the knob is a female head with white flesh.
Artist: The Painter of Naples 2585 and his circle
